This repository contains a Jupyter notebook that quantities the
observed distribution of micrometeoroid (uM) impacts on JWST. It then
uses that distribution to Monte-Carlo simulate the future evolution of
the RMS Wavefront Error (WFE) of the JWST Optical Telescope Element
(OTE). To setup a conda environment for running this notebook, see
e.g., Appendix A of "OTE Science Performance Memo 5: The Optimal
Wavefront Sensing Cadence" (van der Marel, 2025).
